<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>The Poison Inside the Word</title>
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Playfair+Display:wght@400;700;900&family=IBM+Plex+Mono:wght@400;500&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
<style>
  * { margin: 0; padding: 0; box-sizing: border-box; }

  body {
    background: #0e0c0a;
    color: #e8e0d4;
    font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace;
    min-height: 100vh;
    padding: 40px 20px;
    position: relative;
    overflow-x: hidden;
  }

  body::before {
    content: '';
    position: fixed;
    inset: 0;
    background: 
      radial-gradient(ellipse at 10% 20%, rgba(180,60,30,0.08) 0%, transparent 50%),
      radial-gradient(ellipse at 90% 80%, rgba(100,80,40,0.1) 0%, transparent 50%);
    pointer-events: none;
  }

  .container {
    max-width: 860px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .label {
    font-size: 10px;
    letter-spacing: 4px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #b8441a;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  h1 {
    font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif;
    font-size: clamp(36px, 6vw, 72px);
    font-weight: 900;
    line-height: 1.05;
    color: #f0e8dc;
    margin-bottom: 8px;
    letter-spacing: -1px;
  }

  h1 span {
    color: #b8441a;
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .subtitle {
    font-size: 13px;
    color: #7a6e62;
    margin-bottom: 56px;
    letter-spacing: 1px;
  }

  .section-label {
    font-size: 9px;
    letter-spacing: 5px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #5a4e44;
    margin-bottom: 20px;
    padding-bottom: 8px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #2a2420;
  }

  /* Desktop table */
  table {
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    margin-bottom: 56px;
  }

  thead tr {
    background: #1a1612;
  }

  th {
    padding: 16px 20px;
    text-align: left;
    font-size: 9px;
    letter-spacing: 3px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #b8441a;
    font-weight: 500;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #b8441a;
  }

  td {
    padding: 18px 20px;
    font-size: 13px;
    color: #c8bfb2;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #1e1a16;
    line-height: 1.5;
    vertical-align: top;
  }

  tr:hover td {
    background: #141210;
    color: #e0d8cc;
  }

  td:first-child {
    color: #7a6e62;
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 1px;
    white-space: nowrap;
    width: 160px;
  }

  td:nth-child(2) {
    color: #8a7e72;
    text-decoration: line-through;
    text-decoration-color: #b8441a44;
    width: 200px;
  }

  td:nth-child(3) {
    color: #d4ccc0;
  }

  /* Mobile cards */
  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    h1 { font-size: 32px; }
    .subtitle { font-size: 11px; margin-bottom: 36px; }

    table, thead, tbody, th, td, tr { display: block; }

    thead { display: none; }

    tr {
      background: #0a0806;
      border: 1px solid #2a2420;
      border-left: 3px solid #b8441a;
      margin-bottom: 16px;
      padding: 16px;
    }

    td {
      padding: 6px 0;
      border: none;
      font-size: 13px;
      width: 100% !important;
      white-space: normal !important;
    }

    td::before {
      display: block;
      font-size: 8px;
      letter-spacing: 3px;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: #5a4e44;
      margin-bottom: 4px;
    }

    td:first-child::before { content: 'Era'; }
    td:nth-child(2)::before { content: 'Old Gate'; }
    td:nth-child(3)::before { content: 'New Merit Gate'; }

    td:first-child {
      color: #b8441a;
      font-size: 12px;
      font-weight: 500;
    }

    td:nth-child(2) {
      color: #6a5e54;
      width: auto;
    }

    td:nth-child(3) {
      color: #d4ccc0;
    }

    .bottom-line {
      padding: 24px 20px;
    }

    .footer {
      text-align: left;
    }
  }

  .bottom-line {
    background: #0a0806;
    border: 1px solid #2a2420;
    border-left: 3px solid #b8441a;
    padding: 36px 40px;
    margin-bottom: 40px;
  }

  .bottom-line p {
    font-size: 13px;
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: #b8b0a4;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }

  .bottom-line p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .bottom-line strong {
    color: #e8e0d4;
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .footer {
    font-size: 10px;
    color: #3a3430;
    letter-spacing: 2px;
    text-align: right;
  }
</style>
</head>
<body>
<div class="container">

  <div class="label">Historical Analysis</div>
  <h1>The Poison Inside<br>the <span>Word</span></h1>
  <p class="subtitle">Every time "merit" appeared historically, it was replacing one gatekeeping system with another</p>

  <div class="section-label">Era / Old Gate / New "Merit" Gate</div>

  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Era</th>
        <th>Old Gate</th>
        <th>New "Merit" Gate</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td>1853 Britain</td>
        <td>Aristocratic birth</td>
        <td>Oxbridge education</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>1883 USA</td>
        <td>Political loyalty</td>
        <td>Written exams (which favored the already educated)</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Colonial Pakistan</td>
        <td>British preference</td>
        <td>CSS exam (urban elite advantage)</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>EU today</td>
        <td>National patronage</td>
        <td>Multilingual academic credentials</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <div class="bottom-line">
    <p>"Merit" entered governance not to level the field but to <strong>shift who controls the field</strong>. Each new ruling class coined its own definition of merit that happened to look exactly like themselves.</p>
    <p>The word is not poisonous by accident. It was designed to <strong>sound neutral while encoding privilege</strong>.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="footer">From conversation on governance, merit &amp; systems &mdash; 2026</div>

</div>
</body>
</html>